• For unarmed strike use the basic Melee Attack Check and subtract 4, since unarmed counds as a light weapon for this.

Step Three:
• If you beat the defender, the defender is disarmed.
• If you attempted the disarm unarmed, you now have the weapon.
• If you were armed, the defender's weapon is on the ground in the defender's square.
• If you failed the disarm, defender may react and attempt to disarm you with opposed melee attack rolls, and does not provoke an attack of opportunity.
